American defender Ella Stephan has signed for Scottish champions Glasgow City after leaving Russian outfit Ryazan.

Stephan, 24, has played for the USA at under-17, under-20 and under-23 level.

She played for Florida State University before joining American W League outfit Pali-Blues.

Stephan's capture comes as head coach Eddie Wolecki Black admitted that City could again lose some of their top players to financially richer leagues.
